{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Zec|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"Then he showed me the high priest Joshua standing before the angel of the Lord, with Satan standing at his right side to accuse him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"The Lord said to Satan, “The Lord rebuke you, Satan! May the Lord who has chosen Jerusalem rebuke you! Isn’t this man a burning stick snatched from the fire?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"Now Joshua was dressed with filthy clothes as he stood before the angel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"So the angel of the Lord spoke to those standing before him, “Take off his filthy clothes!” Then he said to him, “See, I have removed your iniquity from you, and I will clothe you with festive robes.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"Then I said, “Let them put a clean turban on his head.” So a clean turban was placed on his head, and they clothed him in garments while the angel of the Lord was standing nearby.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"Then the angel of the Lord charged Joshua,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"“This is what the Lord of Armies says: If you walk in my ways and keep my mandates, you will both rule my house and take care of my courts; I will also grant you access among these who are standing here.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"“Listen, High Priest Joshua, you and your colleagues sitting before you; indeed, these men are a sign that I am about to bring my servant, the Branch.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"Notice the stone I have set before Joshua; on that one stone are seven eyes. I will engrave an inscription on it” —this is the declaration of the Lord of Armies —“and I will take away the iniquity of this land in a single day.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"On that day, each of you will invite his neighbor to sit under his vine and fig tree.” This is the declaration of the Lord of Armies.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,5,6,8],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Fourth Vision: High Priest and Branch"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then he showed me the high priest Joshua "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Hg 1:1","book":"Hag","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Hg 1:12","book":"Hag","chapter":1,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Hg 1:14","book":"Hag","chapter":1,"verse":14,"letter":"c"},{"kind":